place","    @DropOnFailure var offers: [LoanOffer]         \/\/ failed elements → removed","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Every stored property without an annotation is implicitly "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/LenientCodable\/documentation\/LenientCodable\/NilOnFailure()","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", which requires the type to have a nil-shaped hole for the failure to land in — "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"T?"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"[T?]"},{"type":"text","text":", or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"[T?]?"},{"type":"text","text":". Any other shape is a compile error with fix-its, so "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"nothing is silently strict and nothing is silently lenient","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": every property’s failure behavior is readable at its declaration, and the compiler enforces that the accounting is complete."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The one-sentence philosophy: "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"lenient about values, strict about structure — and you pick per property whether “strict” means throw."}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Choosing an annotation","anchor":"Choosing-an-annotation"},{"header":"row","type":"table","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Annotation"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Applies to","type":"text"}]}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On failure"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Can fail the decode?"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"(none)"}]},{"type":"text","text":" \/ "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/LenientCodable\/documentation\/LenientCodable\/NilOnFailure()"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"T?"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"[T?]"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"[T?]?"}]}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" exactly where it broke"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"never"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/LenientCodable\/documentation\/LenientCodable\/DropOnFailure()","type":"reference","isActive":true}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"[T]"}]}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"element removed, order kept"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"never"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/LenientCodable\/documentation\/LenientCodable\/Strict()","type":"reference"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"any type"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"throws","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"yes — the only way","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"}]}]]]},{"level":3,"anchor":"Observability","text":"Observability","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Leniency without observability would just be silent data loss. In DEBUG builds every absorbed failure — including missing keys — is logged via "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"os.Logger"},{"type":"text","text":" under subsystem "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"LenientCodable"},{"type":"text","text":", category "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"decoding"},{"type":"text","text":"; an explicit JSON "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"null"},{"type":"text","text":" is the one intentional silent case. Release builds compile the logging out entirely."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"sh","code":["log stream --predicate 'subsystem == \"LenientCodable\"' --level error"],"type":"codeListing"}],"kin